        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 6:08PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chalk Hills, or 15 miles south of Grandview, and 5 to 10 miles west
of State highway 51, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause ponding on the
highway near ShooFly Cutoff, and also on Mud Flat Rd.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Bruneau around 610 PM MDT.
Bruneau Sand Dunes around 620 PM MDT.
Hammett around 640 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
